sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Python SDK
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>Watch/Reconcile
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>mTLS
    participant Volcano as Volcano Scheduler<br/>Optional
    participant HPA as HPA Controller<br/>Metrics-based
    participant Pods as Training Pods<br/>Worker/Master

    Note over User,Pods: Flow 1: Training Job Creation

    User->>K8sAPI: POST PyTorchJob/TFJob/MPIJob<br/>Auth: User credentials/ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate/Mutate CR<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validated CR
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job Created

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch Event (Job Created)<br/>TLS 1.2+ ServiceAccount token

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Pods/Services<br/>HTTPS 6443/TCP<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMaps<br/>HTTPS 6443/TCP<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    Note over Operator,Volcano: Flow 3: Gang Scheduling (Optional)

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create PodGroup<br/>HTTPS 6443/TCP<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI->>Volcano: Watch PodGroup<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Volcano->>K8sAPI: Schedule Pods Atomically<br/>HTTPS 6443/TCP<br/>ServiceAccount token

    K8sAPI-->>Pods: Pods Scheduled & Running

    Note over Operator,HPA: Flow 4: PyTorch Elastic Training with HPA

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create HPA for PyTorchJob<br/>HTTPS 6443/TCP<br/>ServiceAccount token
    HPA->>K8sAPI: Watch Metrics & Scale Replicas<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP<br/>TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI->>Pods: Scale Workers Dynamically

    Pods-->>Pods: Training Coordination<br/>Framework-specific protocol

    Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Metrics Collection

    Operator->>Operator: Export Metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Pods: Job Lifecycle

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update Job Status<br/>HTTPS 6443/TCP
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Cleanup Resources on Completion<br/>HTTPS 6443/TCP
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job Status: Succeeded/Failed
